[background arg="res://Bg/courtyard.png" fade="1.0"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_stands_near.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
Victor stands near the edge of the courtyard, watching students pass by his ignored display.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (animated) left
	join Characters/Victor (half) right
	Celestine: Victor. We need to talk.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victors_eyes_flicker.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Victor's eyes flicker with something - fear? Defiance?
	Victor: I already told you everything I know.
	Celestine: You told me you were home all night. That was a lie.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victors_jaw_tightens.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/controversy.mp3" [loop="true"]
	update Characters/Victor (angry) right
	Victor's jaw tightens.
	Victor: I don't know what you're talking about.
	Celestine: I found a receipt in your sketchbook. Art supply store, 8\:47 PM.
	Celestine: You weren't home. You were out.
	Victor: So I went shopping. That doesn't mean I came here.
	Celestine: Then explain this.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/the_protagonist_holds.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist holds up the paint cloth in a clear bag.
	Celestine: Found at the scene of the crime. Right next to the broken sculpture.
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	join Characters/Victor (half) right
	Conrad: Victor. We need to talk.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victors_eyes_flicker.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Victor's eyes flicker with something - fear? Defiance?
	Victor: I already told you everything I know.
	Conrad: You told me you were home all night. That was a lie.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victors_jaw_tightens.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/controversy.mp3" [loop="true"]
	update Characters/Victor (angry) right
	Victor's jaw tightens.
	Victor: I don't know what you're talking about.
	Conrad: I found a receipt in your sketchbook. Art supply store, 8\:47 PM.
	Conrad: You weren't home. You were out.
	Victor: So I went shopping. That doesn't mean I came here.
	Conrad: Then explain this.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/the_protagonist_holds.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist holds up the paint cloth in a clear bag.
	Conrad: Found at the scene of the crime. Right next to the broken sculpture.
Victor: That could belong to anyone. We all use cloths like that.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: This one has an inventory tag. Number 14-C.
	Celestine: That's your cabinet number, Victor. Your assigned supplies.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victors_face_goes.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	update Characters/Victor (sad) right
	Victor's face goes pale.
	Victor: That... someone must have stolen it. Framed me.
	Celestine: The sketchbook. The receipt. The cloth. Your resentment toward Mia.
	Celestine: At what point do coincidences stop being coincidences?
	Victor: You don't understand!
	Celestine: Then help me understand.
else:
	Conrad: This one has an inventory tag. Number 14-C.
	Conrad: That's your cabinet number, Victor. Your assigned supplies.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victors_face_goes.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Victor's face goes pale.
	Victor: That... someone must have stolen it. Framed me.
	Conrad: The sketchbook. The receipt. The cloth. Your resentment toward Mia.
	Conrad: At what point do coincidences stop being coincidences?
	Victor: You don't understand!
	Conrad: Then help me understand.
join Mark (Mark_half) leftmost
Mark: We're not trying to destroy you, Victor. We just want the truth.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_looks_between.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
Victor looks between them, his defiance crumbling.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/his_hands_begin.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
His hands begin to shake.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	"Celestine (Thinking)": What should I do?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/the_protagonists_tone.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/sad.mp3" [loop="true"]
	Their tone softens.
	Celestine: Victor. I've read your sketchbook.
	Celestine: Not just the angry parts. The technical studies. The hours of practice.
	Celestine: You're talented. Really talented.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_looks_up.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Victor looks up, surprised.
	Celestine: But you've been hurting for a long time. Feeling invisible.
	Celestine: Feeling like no matter how hard you work, no one sees you.
else:
	"Conrad (Thinking)": What should I do?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/the_protagonists_tone.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/sad.mp3" [loop="true"]
	Their tone softens.
	Conrad: Victor. I've read your sketchbook.
	Conrad: Not just the angry parts. The technical studies. The hours of practice.
	Conrad: You're talented. Really talented.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_looks_up.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Victor looks up, surprised.
	Conrad: But you've been hurting for a long time. Feeling invisible.
	Conrad: Feeling like no matter how hard you work, no one sees you.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victors_eyes_begin.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
update Characters/Victor (half) right
Victor's eyes begin to glisten.
Victor: You... you don't know what it's like.
Victor: Every competition, every exhibition, every award. It's always someone else.
Victor: I practice twice as much as anyone. I study the masters. I perfect my technique.
update Characters/Victor (sad) right
Victor: And Mia just... feels her way through it. No discipline. No rigor.
Victor: Yet everyone calls her a genius and ignores me.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: That must be incredibly painful.
else:
	Conrad: That must be incredibly painful.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victors_voice_breaks.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
join Characters/Victor (cry) right
Victor's voice breaks.
Victor: My parents keep asking why I can't be more like her.
Victor: My father says art is a waste of time unless you're the best.
Victor: And I can't be the best. Not with Mia around.
Mark: So you destroyed her sculpture.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_collapses_onto.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
Victor collapses onto a nearby bench, his head in his hands.
Victor: I didn't mean to. I just... I wanted to see it gone.
Victor: I thought if her work disappeared, people would finally look at mine.
Victor: But they didn't. They just kept talking about her. "Poor Mia. Her beautiful sculpture."
Victor: It's always about her.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: You wrote the note. "Not everyone deserves to shine."
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_nods_weakly.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Victor nods weakly.
	Victor: I thought... I thought I deserved to shine. More than her.
	Victor: But now I just feel empty.
	Victor: Destroying her art didn't make mine better. It just made me... this.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_looks_up.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	He looks up at the protagonist, tears streaming down his face.
	Victor: I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.
	Celestine: You need to tell Ms. Reyes. And Mia.
	Victor: I know.
	Celestine: This isn't going to go away. There will be consequences.
else:
	Conrad: You wrote the note. "Not everyone deserves to shine."
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_nods_weakly.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Victor nods weakly.
	Victor: I thought... I thought I deserved to shine. More than her.
	Victor: But now I just feel empty.
	Victor: Destroying her art didn't make mine better. It just made me... this.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_looks_up.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	He looks up at the protagonist, tears streaming down his face.
	Victor: I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.
	Conrad: You need to tell Ms. Reyes. And Mia.
	Victor: I know.
	Conrad: This isn't going to go away. There will be consequences.
Victor: I know that too.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/victor_stands_wiping.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
Victor stands, wiping his eyes.
Victor: I just wanted someone to see me. To say my work mattered.
Victor: But not like this. Never like this.
leave Characters/Victor
leave Mark
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/the_protagonist_stands.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist stands alone in the courtyard, watching Victor walk toward the art room.
	Celestine: Every case teaches something.
	Celestine: But the lessons aren't always easy.
	leave Celestine
else:
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s4/the_protagonist_stands.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist stands alone in the courtyard, watching Victor walk toward the art room.
	Conrad: Every case teaches something.
	Conrad: But the lessons aren't always easy.
	leave Conrad
jump c3s5/